-- Helmerich & Payne CEO to Retire, Lindsay to Take Over
-- B y   T i n a   D a v i s
-- 2013-08-21T16:01:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-21/helmerich-payne-ceo-to-retire-lindsay-to-take-over-correct-.html
(Corrects name of company co-founder in second paragraph.)  Helmerich & Payne Inc. (HP) , the largest
onshore drilling rig contractor in the U.S., said Chief
Executive Officer Hans Helmerich will retire in March and Chief
Operating Officer John W. Lindsay will take over.  Helmerich will remain as chairman and has a three-year
consultancy agreement, the company said in a statement today.
The grandson of company co-founder Walter Helmerich, Hans
Helmerich has been CEO since 1989. He said the decision to step
down after 25 years in charge was made with the board four years
ago.  Lindsay, 52, was promoted to president and COO last year
and has been with the Tulsa, Oklahoma-based company since 1987.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tina Davis in  New York  at 
